threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is an ARM-based botnet agent, likely a variant of the Mirai family. The binary exhibits several malicious behaviors: it checks for `.onion` domains for C2 communication over Tor (in function `sub_e6d0`), detaches from the terminal by redirecting its I/O to `/dev/null` (in `sub_1f5cc`), and uses obfuscated strings to hide its functionality. It also contains logic to construct network packets (`http/1.1` string in `sub_1bcc4`), likely for C2 communication or performing attacks.
